<TITLE> EC to take action against CDA chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 5 (bdnews24.com) The Election Commission will take action against chairman of the Chittagong Development Authority (CDA) Abdus Salam for accompanying a mayoral candidate of the June 17 city corporation election, an official said Saturday. Returning officer Jasmine Tuli on Saturday sent a letter to the EC secretary for taking action against him, he said. The CDA chairman took part in the election campaign at Mohra area of the port city on Friday on behalf of ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury, the former mayor, who is contesting the polls under the banner of Nagorik Committee. City corporation returning officer Md Farhad Hossain told bdnews24.com: "We have received information of the CDA chairman's participating in the election campaign through photographs and reports published in dailies and from our own source." "It is a violation of the electoral code." Under section 6(14) of the election code, no government official can participate in an election campaign. He also said a letter signed by the returning officer was sent to the secretary of the election commission. A copy of the letter will also be sent to the CDA chairman, the official said. bdnew
